summary: Hate to burst everyone’s bubble but both Peters in the MCU have a thing about dead dads/father figures. Ego and Yondu on Quill's...
body:
Hate to burst everyone’s bubble but both Peters in the MCU have a thing about dead dads/father figures. Ego and Yondu on Quill’s end and Ben and Tony on Parker’s end (and I guess Richard Parker too). Plus, they both had to watch their main father figures die in front of them without being able to do anything about it.

Also, they both have to fight their girlfriends’ dads so there’s that too

Idk there’s a weird emphasis on fathers in their personal arcs, more so with Parker than Quill with all the Far From Home stuff but it’s probably because Tony’s the bigger character in the main plot than Yondu

summary: I still find it bull crap that out of ALL the heroes remaining in the MCU, Nick Fury recruits Spider-Man because no one else is...
body:
I still find it bull crap that out of ALL the heroes remaining in the MCU, Nick Fury recruits Spider-Man because no one else is available.

Including those who are more skilled and experienced in fighting against the Elementals.

I mean, I get Peter’s an Avenger (kinda, sorta), and maybe there’s a legit reason Fury recruits him but he’s still a 16 year old teenager who’s still grieving over the loss of his mentor, and just wants to take a break for a little while. There’s nothing wrong with that!

But, NOPE! Things just can’t go his way just this once can they!
